  "commentary": "With SPX at 6594.64 sitting right between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-24.6B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+21.1B), dealers are currently buying the slight dip from this morning's highs, creating upward pressure. The BREAKOUT regime with -48.1B total GEX means any directional move will be amplified by dealer hedging - if we break below 6590, expect accelerated selling as dealers short more delta, while a push above 6605 should trigger dealer selling into strength. Watch the 6590-6605 range closely as the pivot zone, with heavy negative gamma walls stacked below (6580, 6585, 6575) that will amplify any breakdown.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile swings between 6590-6605 with big moves if either level breaks.",
